        Az10DaysD3: "Day 3: Baku-Guba-Khinalig-Guba (300 km)",
        Az10DaysP3:
          "This morning we will leave Baku for Guba.  The trip takes 2.5- 3 hours. Upon arrival in Guba you will have a walking city tour. We will drive towards Caucasus Mountains to Khinalig village. The village of Khinalig is an ancient settlement, going back to the Caucasian Albanian period. Khinalig is the highest, most remote and isolated village in Azerbaijan (all tour to Guba and Khinalig depend on the weather conditions). We will visit an ethnographic museum. Overnight at the hotel in Guba. (B/-/-)",
        Az10DaysD4: "Day 4: Guba- Baku-Shemakha-Nidj-Sheki (480 km)",
        Az10DaysP4:
          "Today in the morning we will visit Red Village inhabited with Jewish minority. Mountain Jews had settled in the Caucasus more than two thousand years ago, and appeared on the Azerbaijan land only in the 5th century. Red Village is famous not only for being an oasis of unique national culture, but also its natives. We will visit the Museum of Mountain Jews (closed on Saturdays). Then we will visit the Memorial Complex of Genocide on our way back to Baku. Leaving Baku behind us, our journey takes us through beautiful landscapes on the way to Shemakha. Upon arrival in Shemakha we will have a sightseeing of historical Djuma Mosque. Also we will visit mausoleum of Diri Baba in Maraza and ancient mausoleum and cemetery Yeddi Gumbez. After Shemakha we will visit the village of Nidzh, not far from Gabala, is known for a unique architectural monument of the Caucasian Albania - Udin Temple. The udins are absolutely special ethnic group who are considered descendants of Albanians. We will visit also the house museum of Udins with their traditions, language and history. Arrival in Sheki. Overnight in Sheki. (B/-/-)",
