          "Before leaving Sheki, we will go to Sheki’s Teze Bazaar, with its overflowing stalls of spice and fresh produce. After that, we will leave Sheki and travel to see one of the main historical and architectural cities – Ganja. Ganja is the second largest city in the country, a monument of the ancient culture. We will visit the “Bottle House”. In 1966-67, Ganja resident Ibrahim Jafarov used unusual material-glass bottles in the construction of his house. Totally 48,000 bottles of various shapes and sizes were used in the construction, and he also used colored stones brought from Sochi. Also we will see the 17th century Shah Abbas Mosque, Javad khan Mausoleum (XIX century), the Orthodox Church (1815). We will see Nizami Mausoleum and Imamzade Mosque. Overnight at the hotel in Ganja.(B/-/-)",
        Az10DaysD7: "Day 7: Ganja-Baku-Lankaran (370 km)",
        Az10DaysP7:
          "We will leave Ganja for Baku. Arrival in Baku. On the way to Lankaran we will visit the Gobustan Historical Reserve (65 km far). The reserve is a national historical landmark of Azerbaijan established to preserve the prehistoric rock carvings, mud volcanoes and musical stones in the region. Before the start of the tour around Gobustan we will visit the interactive museum with the same name, where with the help of special programs and multimedia touch screens we will get information about the nature, the flora of Gobustan. Gobustan was inscribed in the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2007. Azerbaijan has the highest number of mud volcanoes in the world. Not far from Gobustan lies the mud volcanoes.  We will visit mud volcanoes (depending on the weather conditions). Arrival in Lankaran. Overnight at the hotel in Lankaran. (B/-/-)",
        Az10DaysD8: "Day 8: Lankaran-Baku (250 km)",
        Az10DaysP8:
          "Today you will depart with your driver and guide for Baku. Before the departure to Baku, we will drive to Astara. We will visit Yanar Bulag (Burning water). It consists of a metal stand pipe inside a small pavilion through which water comes gurgling out. When you light a match and touch the water, the water itself is set ablaze. This occurs due to water's high methane content. The locals believe the water from the spring has remedial properties, and would often take a drink while the flame is alight. After that, we will back to Baku. Arrival in Baku. Overnight at the hotel in Baku. (B/-/-)",
        Az10DaysD9: "Day 9: Baku City Tour",
        Az10DaysP9:
          "After breakfast we will visit Azerbaijani National Carpet Museum (closed on Mondays). It was the first specialized museum of carpets in the world. In 2017, the Azerbaijani National Carpet Museum was awarded the Best Experience award in the field of intangible cultural heritage database by the International Council of Museums. We will visit Zeynalabdin Taghiyev’s palace (closed on Mondays). This palace previously belonged to Azerbaijani millionaire Zeynalabdin Tagiyev. Also we will visit Villa Petrolea constructed in 1884, it was a residence for Nobel brothers for almost 40 years. Then, we will visit Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center (closed on Mondays). The building was designed by worldwide recognized Iraqi-British architect and Pritzker Prize winner Zaha Hadid in 2012. The building's design is characterized by its futuristic and fluid forms, featuring curves, waves, and a smooth white exterior. It has won numerous international architectural awards for its innovative and striking design. Overnight at the hotel in Baku.(B/-/-)",
        Az10DaysD10: "Day 10: Departure",
